<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4329.4.1>
    bibo:endPage "326" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2017-10-06" ;
    bibo:startPage "301" ;
    bibo:volume "4329" ;
    dc:creator "Gower, David J." ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "A new species of small and highly abbreviated caecilian (Gymnophiona: Indotyphlidae) from the Seychelles island of Praslin, and a recharacterization of Hypogeophis brevis Boulenger, 1911" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002952>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002964>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002968>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002966>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002970> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002952>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Maps showing sampling distribution: (a) Mahé Hypogeophis brevis (grey symbols): circles indicate collecting localities between 2013 and 2015 (BMNH), and triangles indicate approximate collecting localities between 1976 and 1991 (UMMZ), and (b) Praslin H. pti sp. nov. (red symbols)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1002952/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002964>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Holotype of Hypogeophis pti sp. nov. (BMNH 2005.1825). Scale bar increments in mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1002964/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002968>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. The 14 types of Hypogeophis pti sp. nov., showing head and collars in dorsal and right lateral views. All specimen numbers with “ BMNH 2005. ” prefix: (a) 1834, (b) 1831, (c) 1828, (d) 1833, (e) 1836, (f) 1830, (g) 1826, (h) 1838, (i) 1825, the holotype, (j) 1832, (k) 1829, (l) 1827, (m) 1835, (n) 1837. Specimens in (a) – (f) male; (g) – (k) female. Scale bars 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1002968/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002966>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. (a) Histogram depicting the frequency of the number of vertebrae, (b) box plot summarising variation in the ratio between eye-tentacle / eye-naris distances for Hypogeophis brevis (grey) and H. pti sp. nov. (black), (c) Principal components analysis (PCA), and (d) principal coordinate analysis (PCoA) for all head measurements for H. brevis (grey circles) and H. pti sp. nov. (black squares)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1002966/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1002970>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Twelve of the 13 paratypes of Hypogeophis pti sp. nov., showing posteriormost part of body in ventral view (the posterior end of the body is missing in the remaining paratype). All specimen numbers with “ BMNH 2005. ” prefix: (a) 1834, (b) 1831, (c) 1828, (d) 1833, (e) 1836, (f) 1830, (g) 1826, (h) 1838, (i) 1829, (j) 1832, (k) 1837, (l) 1835. Specimens in (a) – (f) male; (g) – (j) female. Scale bars 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1002970/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

